00:16:56.110 --> 00:17:07.660
for your words regarding our
program today and Derrick Beard.

00:17:07.660 --> 00:17:16.560
And so now we will move
on to our first panel

00:17:16.560 --> 00:17:21.520
which covers the importance of
the autobiography of Omar Said,

00:17:21.520 --> 00:17:25.490
a west African scholar who
was captured in 1807 and sold

00:17:25.490 --> 00:17:29.040
to South Carolina as a slave.

00:17:29.040 --> 00:17:35.810
He wrote his autobiography
in 1831.

00:17:35.810 --> 00:17:43.700
And this remains the only
known one at this time

00:17:43.700 --> 00:17:45.510
in existence in the US.

