01:42:12.030 --> 01:42:14.990
My question is this
Arabic manuscript

01:42:14.990 --> 01:42:17.600
of our elder Omar Said.

01:42:17.600 --> 01:42:22.870
Is it in the Fusa
Arabic or local Arabic?

01:42:22.870 --> 01:42:26.570
And do we find the
names of his teachers?

01:42:26.570 --> 01:42:34.270
&gt;&gt; Dr. Ala Alryyes: He does
mention the name of his teachers

01:42:34.270 --> 01:42:39.570
and he actually refers to their
names and he refers to one

01:42:39.570 --> 01:42:42.040
of them as his own brother.

01:42:42.040 --> 01:42:43.910
One thing that we need
to remember about Omar,

01:42:43.910 --> 01:42:46.300
and this is really
critically important about him

01:42:46.300 --> 01:42:51.720
and about someone else who
was also a friend of his

01:42:51.720 --> 01:42:56.780
and someone whose title
on the title page is

01:42:56.780 --> 01:43:01.860
that these men's native
languages were not Arabic,

01:43:01.860 --> 01:43:03.160
right?

01:43:03.160 --> 01:43:05.520
These men were Africans
and they spoke --

01:43:05.520 --> 01:43:08.620
that's right, they
spoke local languages.

01:43:08.620 --> 01:43:12.290
So they have their own
obviously mother tongue.

01:43:12.290 --> 01:43:16.490
Arabic was the language of
scholarship and literacy

01:43:16.490 --> 01:43:19.400
in the same way shall we say
that Latin was the language

01:43:19.400 --> 01:43:24.570
of scholarship in Europe
for a very long time, right?

01:43:24.570 --> 01:43:33.320
And so that's one thing that
needs to be I think mentioned

01:43:33.320 --> 01:43:38.520
at this time and I think
fits into your question.

01:43:38.520 --> 01:43:43.450
The other thing is about the
level of the register of Arabic.

01:43:43.450 --> 01:43:46.490
And yes, the register
is [inaudible], right?

01:43:46.490 --> 01:43:47.790
The register is Ahi.

01:43:47.790 --> 01:43:49.090
It's not a demotic.

01:43:49.090 --> 01:43:50.480
It's not a local dialect.

01:43:50.480 --> 01:43:55.400
It's really a Fusa,
formal Arabic.

01:43:55.400 --> 01:43:56.700
&gt;&gt; Dr. Eugene Flanagan: Thanks.

01:43:56.700 --> 01:43:58.360
Oh, sorry, Adam.

01:43:58.360 --> 01:43:59.660
Please.

01:43:59.660 --> 01:44:00.990
&gt;&gt; Dr. Aldam Rothman: At the
