01:52:48.700 --> 01:52:51.330
But people whose knowledge

01:52:51.330 --> 01:52:55.490
of Arabic was actually
much better than Omar's.

01:52:55.490 --> 01:53:01.680
And who also quote
a number of books

01:53:01.680 --> 01:53:05.700
that they had read
before they were enslaved.

01:53:05.700 --> 01:53:14.610
And so you see really kind
of an elite of scholars,

01:53:14.610 --> 01:53:20.120
people who have attained a
high level of scholarship.

01:53:20.120 --> 01:53:27.920
And we find that in Brazil and
in some other countries as well.

01:53:27.920 --> 01:53:32.800
Now when there was just
very briefly this mention

01:53:32.800 --> 01:53:40.670
of conversion in Jamaica, there
is a case for example of a man,

01:53:40.670 --> 01:53:43.590
a Muslim, who converted.

01:53:43.590 --> 01:53:51.690
And what that gave him was
access to paper, to notebooks.

01:53:51.690 --> 01:53:59.400
And in one of them he wrote
a 50-page treatise on how

01:53:59.400 --> 01:54:04.870
to remain a good Muslim,
these kind of things,

01:54:04.870 --> 01:54:08.750
and how to preserve
the community.

01:54:08.750 --> 01:54:12.800
You has missionaries also

01:54:12.800 --> 01:54:19.490
who gave Bibles in
Arabic to Muslims.

01:54:19.490 --> 01:54:22.420
And that was for them --

01:54:22.420 --> 01:54:28.830
you know, that was great
because you could read.

01:54:28.830 --> 01:54:36.120
Omar also had -- some
also received Korans.

01:54:36.120 --> 01:54:42.850
And in Brazil actually the
Muslims organized themselves

01:54:42.850 --> 01:54:49.180
to have Korans in Arabic
imported from France.

01:54:49.180 --> 01:54:53.770
And people who were
enslaved bought the Korans

01:54:53.770 --> 01:54:59.760
by installments, taking years
sometimes to actually buy them.

01:54:59.760 --> 01:55:05.400
And then the organized
networks from Rio to Bia

01:55:05.400 --> 01:55:10.960
to send those Korans
to other Muslims.

