up on that,

03:56:19.170 --> 03:56:22.030
but the more we discuss it,
that's just critical to know

03:56:22.030 --> 03:56:28.210
with all the things that
we get for the library.

03:56:28.210 --> 03:56:34.350
&gt;&gt; Marieta Harper: My
guess may be Derrick Beard,

03:56:34.350 --> 03:56:41.270
because of his ability
and experience

03:56:41.270 --> 03:56:51.570
with collecting various
artifacts, rare books, items,

03:56:51.570 --> 03:56:55.950
he may be the person
that did that.

03:56:55.950 --> 03:56:58.230
But this is my wild guess.

03:56:58.230 --> 03:57:01.880
Because of his rich background

03:57:01.880 --> 03:57:05.670
in collecting antiques
and so forth.

03:57:05.670 --> 03:57:08.460
And someone like that
from his background --

03:57:08.460 --> 03:57:17.140
I didn't read everything
that this man had the ability

03:57:17.140 --> 03:57:20.710
or knowledge of to do that.

03:57:20.710 --> 03:57:27.010
Because he did a lot of
sharing of the manuscripts,

03:57:27.010 --> 03:57:32.020
not only Omar Ibn Said but
the others in the group.

03:57:32.020 --> 03:57:34.360
And that's a guess.

03:57:34.360 --> 03:57:37.180
But I think that's
an educated guess.

03:57:37.180 --> 03:57:39.150
&gt;&gt; Sylvia Albro: Well, these
things are always puzzles.

03:57:39.150 --> 03:57:40.760
&gt;&gt; Marieta Harper: Yeah.

03:57:40.760 --> 03:57:42.770
&gt;&gt; Domenico Sergi: I don't think
it could be Beard, Marieta,

03:57:42.770 --> 03:57:47.830
and the reason why is because
we know that the cover was sewed

03:57:47.830 --> 03:57:58.310
on by Cothiel 20 years after
the manuscript was made.

03:57:58.310 --> 03:58:02.540
And so that would have been
in the mid-19th century.

03:58:02.540 --> 03:58:08.410
So that thread that was hidden
inside couldn't have been put

03:58:08.410 --> 03:58:09.710
on after the cover.

03:58:09.710 --> 03:58:12.550
It had to go on before.

03:58:12.550 --> 03:58:17.400
So it does tell you
perhaps the time

03:58:17.400 --> 03:58:19.810
that those other
manuscripts were collected.

03:58:19.810 --> 03:58:23.720
But there's also documentation
about those that's in writing.

03:58:23.720 --> 03:58:26.870
So it's just a material clue.

03:58:26.870 --> 03:58:32.390
But I think material clues
have their own contribution.

